cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the automatic interpretation of chest X-rays using deep learning approaches, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves generating rich sentence-level descriptors of findings seen in AP chest X-rays, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses building classifiers for these findings using deep learning classifiers, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper involves crowdsourcing of clinician annotations, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
